      {
        "content": "\ud83c\udfad Welcome to the Formal Debate!\n\n\ud83d\udccb **Topic**: What is the nature of true knowledge?\n\n\ud83d\udc65 **Participants and Positions**:\n  \u2022 Socrates: Knowledge comes from questioning and self-examination\n  \u2022 Student: Knowledge comes from education and learning from others\n\n\ud83d\udcdc **Debate Format** (traditional):\n1. Main Arguments - Each participant makes 1 arguments\n\n\u2696\ufe0f **Rules**:\n  \u2022 Participants must argue for their assigned position\n\nLet us begin! Socrates, please present your opening statement.",
        "additional_kwargs": {},
        "response_metadata": {},
        "type": "human",
        "name": null,
        "id": "ef2e8ee5-738d-43f7-88db-44e07ca3d543",
        "example": false
      },
      {
        "content": "Can we truly say we possess knowledge if we have not questioned it ourselves? Consider, if one's understanding is merely borrowed from others, how can it be certain or true? Is it not through questioning and self-examination that we come to know ourselves and the world around us?",
        "additional_kwargs": {
          "refusal": null
        },
